Creating a "Renesas EMEV" device to build upon AOSP

-----------------------
1) Download AOSP source code follwong the steps 

 http://source.android.com/source/downloading.html

using version "2.3.6_r1" for the repo init" step:

 repo init -u https://android.googlesource.com/platform/manifest -b android-2.3.6_r1

Then define an environment varialble to same the AOSP entry dir, where you have just donwloaded the source:
E.g. 

 export AOSP=~/Android/aosp

-----------------------
2) Clone Renesas custom repositories

For each repository of those listed below:

GitHub repository                    AOSP location
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - 
ffxx68/Renesas-device_emev           device/renesas/emev   OK
ffxx68/Renesas-hardware_libhardware  hardware/libhardware  OK
ffxx68/Renesas-frameworks_base       frameworks/base       OK
ffxx68/Renesas-bionic                bionic                ...
ffxx68/Renesas-build                 build

clone the repository locally, with:

cd $AOSP
git clone git@github.com:<GitHub repository>.git <AOSP location>

Note 1 - I mean "ffxx68/Renesas-device_emev" to be the "entry point" of the entire Renesas "MyPad" project, with the present README explaining the procedure to build the firmware update package from scratch.
